I'd frequented Mr. VJ's barbeque restaurant growing up and had not had a bite in several years and decided to stop by for a family take out order. I called to confirm if the restaurant was open for business in lieu of the Covid-19 pandemic. I arrived and preceded to open the restaurant's screened door to place  my order. I was stopped and asked by the employee to wait outdoors for 15 mins. As a health care professional I totally appreciate all businesses that comply with state orders in an effort to keep their establishment safe for customers and employees. As I'm patiently waiting outdoors, in the heat for well over 20 mins, I'm witnessing other customers walking in and not coming out which was baffling  to me because I thought I was asked to stand outside to reduce crowding indoors. So I returned to the screened door and asked the employee would it be better for me to call in my order. The employee responds by saying, "no, it's first come first serve". I've always been a huge supporter of small Black-owned businesses, but what I won't do is entertain unprofessionalism.
